nodes.title: Guide
widgets_values:
Step 1: Set your desired Sampler, Scheduler in the green area. Set your Base CFG and tweak the CFG range in the light blue area below it.

Step 2: Choose a Checkpoint from the drop down in the dark blue area. Toggle a separate VAE (optional, most are baked in) and any LoRAs into the inputs. SDXL ControlNet and SD1.5 are available on the far right. You have to toggle them on.

Step 3: Ideal SDXL image sizes
1024 x 1024 - 1048576 pixels
1152 x 896  - 1032192 pixels
1216 x 832  - 1011712 pixels
1344 x 768  - 1032192 pixels
1536 x 640  - 983040  pixels

Step 4: Write a new prompt, toggle Output to the green Random, Seed to Randomize, check Extra Options and Auto Queue, press Queue Prompt and let that run. Tweak the prompt as needed. Stretch your legs.

Step 5: Turn off Auto Queue, drag your best random image into this window, change Randomize back to Fixed, drag a new Output toggle to light blue CFG, queue and review some variations.

Step 5: Drag your favorite image into this window, Output to the purple Upscale, change the Upscale CFG to that one, and see some final options.

Step 7: Quick Upscale below in blue is available for refining the denoise of your final upscale.

If you're done with this guide, use this node as scratch paper. :-)
